text: Jürgen Kühling (April 27, 1934 – December 16, 2019) was a German judge and politician. He was a judge in the Federal Constitutional Court of Germany between 1989 and 2001. He was born in Osnabrück, Germany. Kühling died on December 16, 2019 in Hamburg at the age of 85.Der ehemalige Richter des Bundesverfassungsgerichts Dr. Jürgen Kühling ist verstorben ==References== Category:German judges Category:1934 births Category:2019 deaths
